
Release 1.0.1, Thu Oct 18 09:34:00 CEST 2001

This archive contains some tools usefull for a user of PCSC user.
PCSC can be obtained from [1].

The tools provided are:
- pcsc_scan (Ludovic Rousseau <ludovic.rousseau@free.fr>
	regularly scans every PCSC reader connected to the host
	if a card is inserted or removed a line is printed

	For example:

	PC/SC device scanner
	V 1.0.0 (c) 2001, Ludovic Rousseau <ludovic.rousseau@free.fr>
	PCSC lite version: 1.0.0B
	0: GemPC410 0 0

	Tue Oct 16 09:49:48 2001
	 Reader 0 (GemPC410 0 0)
			Card state: State has changed, Card inserted, 
			ATR: 3B 68 00 00 80 66 A2 06 02 01 32 0E 

	Tue Oct 16 09:49:51 2001
	 Reader 0 (GemPC410 0 0)
			Card state: State has changed, Card removed, 

- scriptor.pl (Lionel Victor <lionel.victor@unforgettable.com>)
	 A Perl script to send commands to a smart card. You can use a file
	containing the commands or stdin.

- gscriptor.pl (Lionel Victor <lionel.victor@unforgettable.com>)
	A Perl script to send commands to a smart card with GTK-based
	 graphical interface.

[1] http://linuxnet.com/middle.html

$Id: README,v 1.3 2001-10-18 07:34:14 rousseau Exp $

